                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Montreal</placeName>\n                <date>12th May 5624</date>.</p>\n            <p>\n                <sic>\n                    <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leser</addressee>\n                </sic>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">The Occident for <date>May</date> only<lb/> reached here yesterday\n                afternoon. I have read<lb/> the first portion of the Biography published, and<lb/>\n                find a few errors which I note elsewhere. I<lb/> perceive a query has been attached\n                to an extract<lb/> from one of my ancestors (7 lines from <add>?</add>)<lb/> If this\n                is done purposely, I assure you the<lb/> extract is quite in the good old style, and\n                this<lb/> leads me to ask you to communicate with me<lb/> if you observe anything in\n                the M.S. you do not<lb/> clearly make out or do not wish to publish.<lb/> I send you\n                herewith another <sic>instalment</sic> that<lb/> you may have time to write me\n                before<lb/> going to press, as I have a weakness in always<lb/> wishing to see my\n                M.S. published without added<lb/> comment. Private remarks I will always gladly<lb/>\n                receive.</p>\n            <p>In printing off the sheets for<lb/> a pamphlet, I trust you will omit the<lb/>\n                headings either “The Occident” or “Biography &amp;c”<lb/> and insert the proper\n                pages. I need scarcely<lb/> add that I trust the matter will run on<lb/> so as not\n                to appear having been published<lb/> at intervals. Although intended for\n                presentation<lb/> to the family &amp; friends of my father <add>?</add>, still<lb/>\n                I would like the Biography to appear in neat</p>\n            <p rend=\"The following is written sideways on the left side of the page.\">I have had to\n                delay sending you the MS of the Biography, I am getting it copied at\n                    <persName>Mrs<lb/> De Sola's</persName> leisure (I hate copying) having feared\n                the first part sent you had gone wrong. I have<lb/> also been closely engaged these\n                last few weeks.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32b8vz2z/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
