                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32b8vz2z/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>form, &amp; as I before said, not as if it had<lb/> appeared in the Occident.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have made a search for<lb/> some memorandum or record of payment of<lb/>\n                <persName>Mrs Nadpers</persName> Occident a/c and find none. The<lb/> fact is I\n                never make entries of monies received<lb/> and paid out for others. I have\n                almost<lb/> invariably paid to <persName>Mr J A Joseph</persName> any\n                amount<lb/>—and these have been but few—I have<lb/> received for you, except in one\n                or two<lb/> instances when I sent you money by<lb/>\n                <persName>Mrs Cohen</persName> or <persName>Issak Joseph</persName>. I went to<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr Joseph</persName> and got his clerk and afterward<lb/> himself to look\n                through his books, but<lb/> found nothing. He also has not been accustomed<lb/> to\n                make such entires. As I before wrote<lb/> you I recollect very well <persName>Mrs\n                    A.</persName> having<lb/> paid me—tho' I forgot how much and when.<lb/> I now\n                find in a list made by <persName>Mr J.</persName>\n                <persName>Mrs<lb/> Nadper</persName> is credited in a memorandum in<lb/> my own\n                writing with payment of $9—but<lb/> no mention of the amount having been<lb/>\n                remitted you—this however I have never<lb/> mentioned in any other case. When\n                you<lb/> send your account for the Prayer books<lb/> please add <persName>Mrs\n                    N's</persName> $9 and I will pay<lb/> you in <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >greenbacks</hi> the amount; i.e. if you<lb/> do not object to receive it in\n                your currency.<lb/> You ask what <persName>Benjamins</persName> owe. Here it is.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32b8vz2z/canvas/p2"
                }
